Now that we have the operating cash flow, we can solve for the bid price using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Operating cash flow}&=[(\text{Price}-\text{Variable cost})\times\text{Quantity}] \times (1-\text{Tax rate})\\
&+\text{Tax rate} \times \text{Depreciation}
\end{aligned}$$

The price being referred to in this is the bid price.
